This paper deals with the analysis of the complexity of matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper uses convex optimization, which is a technique commonly used in computational complexity theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also deals with algebraic constructions and tensors, which are related to linear algebra and data structures, respectively. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses information theory to analyze the complexity of matrix multiplication, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses numerical methods to obtain upper bounds on the complexity of matrix multiplication, which makes cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category as well.
